In Security we have 4 types of Operations 
>> Security Duty
>> Security Policy 
>> Security Privilage 
>> Security Role

Security Privilage :- Security privilages are used for the System Access like Screens and Actions
Security Duty      :- These Security Duty are used to group the privilages.
security Policy    :- The Security Policy are used to Filter Records.
Security Role      :- The security Role are used to Assign the roles to users.


Security Privilages :-
>> Nodes inside a Security Privilege (D365FO)

A privilege can contain:

1️⃣ Entry Points
2️⃣ Permissions
3️⃣ Data Entity Permissions
4️⃣ Form Control Permissions
5️⃣ Service Operation Permissions (sometimes visible depending on version)

Entry POints :- 
The purpose of Entry Points is to Navigate and controls the execution.
These are used for the MenuItems of Action,Dispaly,Output. On Forms,Reports,

we need to drag the menuitem on to the entry point and then should change the properties 
1.Access level -- Delete /Read  according to requierment.
2.Object Type -- menuitem Dispaly/output/Action
3.Object Name -- name of the menu item.
4.Grant -- Allow /Deny 


Permissions:-

The permissions are used on the Tables and Views and works for CRUD operations.

Data Entity Permissions:-

>> Controls DMF / OData / Excel Add-in / integrations.
>> Applies to Data Entities.

Used when:
You expose data for import/export
External systems call OData
Excel add-ins are used

Same crud operations.

Form Control Permissions:-
Very granular UI control.
Controls: Buttons , Fields , Tabs , Groups
Overrides default form behavior.
Properties :-
1.ControlName	Name of the form control
2.FormName	Name of the form
3.Enabled	Yes / No
4.Visible	Yes / No
5.Editable	Yes / No



Security Duty :-
A Security Duty groups several Privileges that together let someone perform one functional task.
Example: “Daily Aggregated Data Review”

You might have:

Privilege to open header form
Privilege to open lines form
Privilege to run report
Privilege to delete records

How to create Security Role:
>> navigate to Aot >> security >> Duty >> give name 
add the previlages to it and some of the properties as name and etc.


Security Role:-

Navigaion >> AOT >> Security >> roles >>
Add the Duties to the Roles.


